Brassica campestris

   [3844.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Capparales:Cruciferae
     Synonyms
   Common names irdrape, wild turnip
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3844

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A herbaceous plant with a slender, erect, branched
   stem and a taproot reaching 30-100 cm in height. It has broad-based,
   stem-clasping leaves and the flowers yellow to cream. USES An edible
   oil used in cooking is extracted from the seeds. KILLING TEMP Bird rape
   is resistant to frost at all stages of growth. GROWING PERIOD Annual,
   growing 60-340 days. COMMON NAMES Bird rape, Field mustard, Summer
   turnip rape, Polish rape, Toria, Sarson, Navette d'hiver, Navette
   d'ete. FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: B. campestris var. olifera
   subvar. biennis (winter turnip rape), B. campestris var. olifera
   subvar. annua (summer turnip rape). Seed yields of 3.2-3.5 t/ha are
   considered good, while yields about 1.0-2.2 t/ha are more usual.

   Sources
   SOURCES (B. campestris L.)
   Weiss E 1983 pp 161-215 [TEMP, KTMP, LIG, RAIN, DRA, PH, SAL, TEXT,
   FER]
   Duke J 1975 pp 9 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 336 [USE, TEMP, RAIN, FER, DRA, TEXT, SAL]
   Kernick M 1961 pp 348
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 91 [USE]
   Martin F 1984 pp 78-84 [TEMP, RAIN, PHO, DRA, FER, USE]

